    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - IC BUS SERVICE MANUAL - FLOOR COVERING - REPAIR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REPAIR</title>
        <para>To repair the floor surface use the following procedure:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Determine if floor surface material has a plywood sub-floor. To determine, inspect the side
                door area. Look for a slightly raised trim panel. If present, floor is equipped with plywood
                sub-flooring. See
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700175">Figure 68</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fasteners that secure mat trim; store to re-install</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove damaged area.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure damage area to be repaired for correct sizing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean surface, apply mat adhesive if plywood surface is not suitable, repair with
                appropriate plywood repair.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install surface material.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install trim and fasteners.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Undercoat fasteners that were removed to perform the repair.</para>
        </step1>
